    "updated_at": "2023-05-15T10:00:08Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I thought I'd take a look a this and it looks like Java document the behaviour of `Files.createDirectories()` as throwing `FileAlreadyExistsException` if the directory exists but is not a directory: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/nio/file/Files.html#createDirectories\r\n\r\nThe discussion in https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8130464 confirms that a symlink to a directory is considered \"not a directory\" and as such a `FileAlreadyExistsException` is expected behaviour.\r\n\r\nI've raised PR https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/pull/5453 which resolves the issue on my system by making an additional check that the data directory doesn't exist at all (symlink or otherwise) before creating it and its parents.",
